Based on the results of several review studies in Iran, prevalence of three intestinal parasitic diseases including amoebiasis, cryptosporidiosis and blastocystosis have been reported 1%, 3% and 3%, respectively (
 Badparva et al., 2017; 
 Berahmat et al., 2017; 
 Haghighi et al., 2018). The above mentioned species are the most abundant pathogens for gastroenteritis that occur post-flooding (
 Paterson et al., 2018), so an upswing in the reappearance of these infections in relation with recent flood in the future is predicted.
